title: Boys soccer rankings for Oct. 16, 2015
text:
By Kyle Craig | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 16, 2015 3:30 PM View/Post Comments 
In many ways, it was a week of puzzling scores for lehighvalleylive’s boys soccer rankings. 
The end result, essentially, is the rankings-maker throwing his hands up in the air in frustration with the postseason just around the corner anyway. 
Liberty picked up its second loss of the season in a rivalry contest against Freedom; Moravian Academy played to a scoreless draw with Pleasant Valley; Salisbury fell to Northampton; Freedom lost to Easton; and Central Catholic took an “L” against Allen. 
Considering all of that, the rankings will only have slight alterations with the most important part of the season on the horizon. 
Phillipsburg gets a bump for tying state-ranked Pingry and Warren Hills slides out of the top 10 for now. 
Check out the rankings by scrolling through the gallery atop this post .
